{%- comment -%}
  Ganguram — Checkout shipping-address prefill config (Phase 2.11F.2).

  Publishes window.GanguramCheckoutPrefillConfig and loads
  assets/ganguram-checkout-prefill.js. When the customer selected a full Google
  address in the delivery popup and clicks the STANDARD checkout button, it appends
  the documented checkout[shipping_address][...] parameters (from window.GanguramAddress)
  to the checkout URL so Shopify opens with the shipping address prefilled.

  Standard checkout button only — Shop Pay / dynamic checkout buttons bypass the cart
  form and cannot be prefilled this way (limitation, documented in §9). Respects the
  MOV soft guard; only fills safely-known fields; preserves cart / attributes /
  discounts / payment. Fail-open. Set enabled:false to turn it off. No checkout /
  shipping-rate / ShipZip / SBZ / zipLogic / resolver / settings_data change.
{%- endcomment -%}
<script>
  window.GanguramCheckoutPrefillConfig = {
    enabled: true,
    checkoutUrl: "/checkout"
  };
</script>
<script src="{{ 'ganguram-checkout-prefill.js' | asset_url }}" defer></script>
